# 💡 Support — DigitalMeve

Thanks for using **DigitalMeve**!  
This document explains how to get help depending on your profile (individual, professional, institution).

---

## 📚 Documentation

- [Overview](docs/overview.md) — introduction to `.meve`  
- [Generator Guide](docs/generator-guide.md) — how to create proofs  
- [Verification Guide](docs/verification-guide.md) — how to validate proofs  
- [Specification](docs/specification.md) — formal rules of the format  
- [Security](docs/security.md) — guarantees and threat model  
- [Roadmap](docs/roadmap.md) — upcoming features  

---

## 🙋 Asking Questions

- First check the [Docs](docs/index.md) and [Examples](docs/examples.md).  
- Search [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/BACOUL/digitalmeve/issues).  
- If you don’t find an answer, open a new **Question** issue using the template.  

---

## 🐛 Reporting Bugs

- Use the [Bug Report template](.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.md).  
- Include:  
  - Your Python version (`python --version`)  
  - Your DigitalMeve version (`pip show digitalmeve`)  
  - Steps to reproduce  
  - Error messages and logs  

---

## 💼 Professional & Institutional Support

- **Pro accounts** (companies/freelancers): open a **Feature Request** or contact us at `pro@digitalmeve.com`.  
- **Institutions** (universities, courts, administrations): contact us at `official@digitalmeve.com` for onboarding.  

---

## 🔐 Security Issues

If you discover a vulnerability, please follow our [Security Policy](SECURITY.md).  
📧 Contact: **security@digitalmeve.com** (first response ≤72h).  

---

## 🛠 Contribution Help

See [Contributing Guide](CONTRIBUTING.md) for coding standards, branching, and PR rules.  
PRs are welcome once the CI is green ✅.  

---

✍️ Maintained by the **DigitalMeve Team**.
